      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1509227856,
      "post_id" : 33889423,
      "comment_id" : 80936169,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Never optimize until you actually have a performance problem. More important to be right than fast. And I can&#39;t honestly imagine an application where performance of controlled rounding would be an issue, unless you were Visa or Mastercard (who would just throw more machines at it). And pow() is probably faster than round()."
