      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@ShivakrishnaChippa: yes, because here we specify that we want 2 digits after the comma, and to do a up rounding. In that case, 8.499 is rounded to 8.5. If you want 8.499 to be display, simply set 3 as the maximum fraction digits."
